There were high hopes and great expectations that fateful May 29, 1999. The air was fresh, there was excitement too. The nation heaved a huge sigh of relief: It was a new dawn! The men of jackboots and decrees, were retreating to their barracks. And on their exit, freedom borne on the wings of rule of law, was expected with joyous anticipation. Democracy at last!  New Dawn, Fresh Fears
IT was against that chequered background that the general election was heralded with joy and beautiful anticipations. The Presidential democracy that was ushered in on May 29, 1999 has gone through many electoral cycles. Five epochs have been witnessed by Nigerians. 